HEADWORD: Buffoonery
<hw>Buf*foon"er*y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Buffooneries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>bouffonnerie</ets>.]</ety> <def>The arts and practices of a
buffoon, as low jests, ridiculous pranks, vulgar tricks and
postures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor that it will ever constitute a wit to conclude a tart piece of
<qex>buffoonery</qex> with a ⟦ldquo⟧What makes you blush?⟦rdquo⟧</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buffoonish</ent>⟦br⟧
